# Changelog

All notable changes to the **Document Restoration Tool** will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),  
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).

---

## [3.1.0] - 2026-04-13
### Added
- Finalized **Document Restoration Pipeline v3.1**
- Structured multi-stage workflow:
  - Ingestion → Cleaning → Reconstruction → Output
- Enhanced **text normalization and repair logic**
- Improved handling of:
  - OCR noise
  - Broken formatting
  - Incomplete sentences
- Added modular pipeline components for easier extensibility
- Introduced standardized output formatting for downstream analysis

### Improved
- Significant performance improvements in document parsing
- More accurate sentence boundary reconstruction
- Better handling of edge cases (fragmented or heavily corrupted text)

### Fixed
- Resolved inconsistencies in whitespace normalization
- Fixed rare duplication issues in reconstructed paragraphs
- Corrected encoding-related errors in input processing

---

## [3.0.0] - 2026-03-XX
### Added
- Major architectural redesign of the restoration engine
- Introduction of **multi-pass reconstruction system**
- Separation of concerns between:
  - Raw extraction
  - Semantic reconstruction
  - Output formatting
- Initial support for **batch document processing**

### Improved
- Dramatically improved reconstruction accuracy vs v2.x
- Cleaner and more readable output structure
- Reduced noise propagation through pipeline stages

### Breaking Changes
- Refactored core pipeline interfaces (not backward compatible with v2.x)
- Updated input/output expectations

---

## [2.0.0] - 2026-02-XX
### Added
- First structured **restoration pipeline**
- Basic document cleaning and normalization
- Heuristic-based reconstruction logic
- Support for plain text document ingestion

### Improved
- More consistent formatting of restored text
- Reduction in major OCR artifacts

### Fixed
- Addressed early-stage parsing failures on malformed inputs

---

## [1.1.0] - 2026-01-XX
### Added
- Incremental improvements to text cleaning functions
- Expanded handling of punctuation inconsistencies
- Early-stage formatting normalization

### Improved
- Stability across varied document types
- Reduced crash cases during parsing

---

## [1.0.0] - 2025-12-XX
### Added
- Initial release of **Document Restoration Tool**
- Core functionality:
  - Text ingestion
  - Basic cleaning
  - Simple reconstruction heuristics
- Prototype pipeline for restoring corrupted documents

---

## Notes
- Version 3.1 represents the **first production-ready release** suitable for:
  - Analytical workflows
  - Research pipelines
  - Downstream AI processing
- Future versions will focus on:
  - Multi-document alignment
  - Semantic consistency scoring
  - Integration with audit frameworks
